name: Pumpkin Corn Bread
author: CHRISTI LARSEN
summary: These moist golden orange muffins pair equally well with jam at breakfast or with soups and savory main dishes.
ingredients: ½ cup packed dark brown sugar
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C)
Grease muffin cups or line with paper muffin liners
In a large bowl, stir flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda, and salt and make a well in the center
In a small bowl, stir together the eggs, pumpkin, sugar, and oil
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in the egg mixture
Stir just until blended; do not over mix
Divide the batter evenly among prepared muffin tin cups
Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 18 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into center of a muffin comes out clean
